AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:26:08.080 --> 00:26:09.990
So I'm a user
experience designer.

00:26:09.990 --> 00:26:13.000
And the company
that I work for is--

00:26:13.000 --> 00:26:17.840
so all the people at the top
are men, like most of the time.

00:26:17.840 --> 00:26:20.260
The biggest thing for me
has been that I recently

00:26:20.260 --> 00:26:22.840
had a child, and
I wanted to make

00:26:22.840 --> 00:26:25.540
some sort of minor adjustment
to my working situation.

00:26:25.540 --> 00:26:28.850
I wanted four days a
week instead of five.

00:26:28.850 --> 00:26:31.940
There's tons of data that says
that people that work minorly

00:26:31.940 --> 00:26:34.480
reduced hours are actually
just as productive, if not more

00:26:34.480 --> 00:26:37.030
productive, because
you have good reasons

00:26:37.030 --> 00:26:38.912
to get your stuff
done even better,

00:26:38.912 --> 00:26:41.120
so that you can have that
extra time with, let's say,

00:26:41.120 --> 00:26:44.350
your child, or for whatever
reason you want reduced hours.

00:26:44.350 --> 00:26:47.200
The tech companies are
super against that.

00:26:47.200 --> 00:26:49.680
And I am fighting a
terrible uphill battle

00:26:49.680 --> 00:26:52.020
that I may, in a
few months, decide

00:26:52.020 --> 00:26:55.220
to just quit, because
they're really against it.

00:26:55.220 --> 00:26:58.730
And I don't understand,
from my point of view,

00:26:58.730 --> 00:27:02.220
why they wouldn't even
consider trying it.

00:27:02.220 --> 00:27:03.950
They're just dead
set against it.

00:27:03.950 --> 00:27:06.970
They don't even want to
try it, when wouldn't it

00:27:06.970 --> 00:27:08.710
be in their best
interest to have

00:27:08.710 --> 00:27:11.774
me be happy for a few years
where my child is young,

00:27:11.774 --> 00:27:14.440
and then I will continue to stay
with them, because why wouldn't

00:27:14.440 --> 00:27:17.500
I be 10 times more loyal to
a company that is actually

00:27:17.500 --> 00:27:19.910
working with me, and
what I feel I need

00:27:19.910 --> 00:27:23.460
for my schedule and my sanity,
and my child to grow up

00:27:23.460 --> 00:27:25.710
to see me a little bit more?

00:27:25.710 --> 00:27:27.940
But it's a terrible
uphill battle

00:27:27.940 --> 00:27:30.510
that I have absolutely no
idea how to proceed on.

00:27:30.510 --> 00:27:31.540
ALAINA PERCIVAL: Yeah.

00:27:31.540 --> 00:27:37.030
I mean, this is the kind of
thing that goes back to the,

00:27:37.030 --> 00:27:39.070
hey, it is fiscally responsible.

00:27:39.070 --> 00:27:40.680
It will keep you in your career.

00:27:40.680 --> 00:27:42.350
It's a small thing,
and it's something

00:27:42.350 --> 00:27:45.740
that we are asking
companies to do.

00:27:45.740 --> 00:27:47.660
And it goes back to
what I said earlier.

00:27:47.660 --> 00:27:50.620
Hey, we're realizing that
our power is actually

00:27:50.620 --> 00:27:54.280
going to be in influencing
the companies that support us.

00:27:54.280 --> 00:27:59.170
And the companies want
to know what to do.

00:27:59.170 --> 00:28:09.980
And so creating a list,
or a story of the things

00:28:09.980 --> 00:28:11.750
that need to be
done, companies are

00:28:11.750 --> 00:28:14.850
going to do at least the
easy things, and some

00:28:14.850 --> 00:28:17.980
of the hard things.

00:28:17.980 --> 00:28:20.800
I think that this is
devastating to hear.

00:28:20.800 --> 00:28:23.430
The wonderful thing about
software engineering

00:28:23.430 --> 00:28:27.120
is, actually, it's
incredibly flexible,

00:28:27.120 --> 00:28:30.350
or at least it has the potential
to be incredibly flexible.

00:28:30.350 --> 00:28:33.840
And so when I hear numbers that
women are leaving at a higher

00:28:33.840 --> 00:28:35.554
rate than they are
other industries,

00:28:35.554 --> 00:28:36.720
that should be flip-flopped.

00:28:40.340 --> 00:28:44.760
We should see that women are
staying in tech, in engineering

00:28:44.760 --> 00:28:49.290
positions at a higher rate
than all other industries,

00:28:49.290 --> 00:28:53.370
because you can't be a
pharmacist and work from home.

00:28:53.370 --> 00:29:01.660
Or you can't be a teacher
and come in at 9 o'clock

00:29:01.660 --> 00:29:04.240
and leave at 3:00, and then
work a few hours in the evening.

00:29:04.240 --> 00:29:07.526
But you can do that with tech.

00:29:07.526 --> 00:29:09.400
JULIE PEARL: So we'll
