technical backgrounds.

00:30:01.980 --> 00:30:04.120
The nice thing about
software engineering

00:30:04.120 --> 00:30:08.550
is, hey, what you've
known in the past is still

00:30:08.550 --> 00:30:11.310
going to build on
what you need to know.

00:30:11.310 --> 00:30:13.020
And had you stayed
in the industry,

00:30:13.020 --> 00:30:15.310
you probably would have
learned three new things

00:30:15.310 --> 00:30:18.040
in between the time
that you left and now.

00:30:18.040 --> 00:30:21.370
And I mean, there's always
new languages coming out,

00:30:21.370 --> 00:30:29.600
always new technologies-- web,
now mobile, and Swift, and Go.

00:30:29.600 --> 00:30:32.440
And so you're always
learning something new.

00:30:32.440 --> 00:30:38.210
And so you're in a great
position to reenter the market.

00:30:38.210 --> 00:30:44.350
And you just have to get back
into a programming language

00:30:44.350 --> 00:30:46.030
that interests you.

00:30:46.030 --> 00:30:48.490
